terms.definition: A unit of mass concentration defined as the concentration of one nanogram of a substance per one liter of the mixture, or one picogram of a substance in unit volume of the mixture equal to one milliliter, or one microgram of a substance per one cubic meter of the mixture. The concept also refers to the metric unit of mass density (volumic mass) defined as the density of substance which mass equal to one nanogram occupies the volume one liter.(NCI)
terms.preferredTerm: Nanogram per Liter

terms.definition: Picograms per milliliter (concentration), divided by milligrams per kilogram (dose normalized by body weight).
terms.preferredTerm: Picogram Per Milliliter Per Milligram Per Kilogram

terms.definition: Picograms per milliliter (concentration), divided by milligrams per kilogram per day (daily dose normalized by body weight).
terms.preferredTerm: Picogram Per Milliliter Per Milligram Per Kilogram Per Day

terms.definition: Picograms per milliliter (concentration), divided by micrograms (dose).
terms.preferredTerm: Picogram per Milliliter per Microgram

terms.definition: A unit of a mass fraction expressed as a number of micrograms of substance per kilogram of mixture. The unit is also used as a dose calculation unit.(NCI)
terms.preferredTerm: Microgram per Kilogram

terms.definition: Picograms per milligram creatinine.
terms.preferredTerm: Picogram per Milligram of Creatinine

terms.definition: Picograms per minute.
terms.preferredTerm: Picogram per Minute

terms.definition: A unit of concentration (molarity unit) equal to one trillionth of a mole (10E-12 mole) in one liter of solution.(NCI)
terms.preferredTerm: Picomole per Liter

terms.definition: Picomoles per liter (concentration), divided by micrograms (dose).
terms.preferredTerm: Picomole per Liter per Microgram

terms.definition: Microinternational units per milliliter.
terms.preferredTerm: Microinternational Unit per Milliliter

terms.definition: A unit of volume accepted for use with the SI and equal to one millionth of a liter (10E-6 liter).(NCI)
terms.preferredTerm: Microliter

terms.definition: The unit of mass equal to one millionth of a gram or one thousandth of a milligram.(NCI)
terms.preferredTerm: Microgram

terms.definition: A unit of mass flow rate equivalent to the rate at which one millionth of a gram of matter travels to a given object or space over a period of time equal to twenty four hours. Microgram per day is also a dose administration rate unit equal to the rate at which one millionth of a gram of a product is administered per unit of time equal to twenty four hours.(NCI)
terms.preferredTerm: Microgram per Day

terms.definition: A unit of mass flow rate equivalent to the rate at which one millionth of a gram of matter travels to a given object or space over a period of time equal to one hour.(NCI)
terms.preferredTerm: Microgram per Hour

terms.definition: Micrograms per inhalation.
terms.preferredTerm: Microgram per Inhalation

terms.definition: A unit of mass concentration equal to the concentration of one gram of a substance per unit volume of the mixture equal to one cubic meter. The concept also refers to the metric unit of mass density (volumic mass) defined as the density of substance which mass equal to one gram occupies the volume one cubic meter.(NCI)
terms.preferredTerm: Microgram per Milliliter

terms.definition: Micrograms per milliliter (concentration), divided by milligrams per kilogram (dose normalized by body weight).
terms.preferredTerm: Microgram Per Milliliter Per Milligram Per Kilogram

terms.definition: Micrograms per milliliter (concentration), divided by milligrams per kilogram per day (daily dose normalized by body weight).
terms.preferredTerm: Microgram Per Milliliter Per Milligram Per Kilogram Per Day

terms.definition: Micrograms per milliliter (concentration), divided by milligrams (dose).
terms.preferredTerm: Milligram per Liter per Milligram

terms.definition: A unit of mass flow rate equivalent to the rate at which one millionth of a gram of matter travels to a given object or space over a period of time equal to one minute. Microgram per minute is also a dose administration rate unit equal to the rate at which one millionth of a gram of a product is administered per unit of time equal to one minute.(NCI)
terms.preferredTerm: Microgram per Minute

terms.definition: Micrograms per puff.
terms.preferredTerm: Microgram per Puff

terms.definition: A unit of amount of substance equal to one millionth (10E-6) of a mole.(NCI)
terms.preferredTerm: Micromole

terms.definition: A unit of concentration (molarity unit) equal to one micromole of solute per one liter of solution.
terms.preferredTerm: Nanomole per Milliliter

terms.definition: A unit of amount of substance flow rate equivalent to the rate at which one millionth of a mole of substance travels to a given object or space over a period of time equal to 24 hours.(NCI)
terms.preferredTerm: Micromole per 24 Hours

terms.definition: Micromoles per hour.
terms.preferredTerm: Micromole per Hour

terms.definition: Micromoles per minute.
terms.preferredTerm: Micromole per Minute
